# Keep the refresh image (docker/refresh.Dockerfile) build context small.
#
# That image's build context is the repo ROOT (compose: `context: ..`), but the
# image only COPYs build.py / scrape-rcp.py / refresh-service.py / src/rcp.html.
# Without these excludes the context would include dist/ (~720M) and data/
# (~260M): every `docker compose up --build` would tar and ship ~1GB to the
# daemon, which is slow and can FAIL the build on a small VPS ("no space left on
# device"), aborting `up` so no containers get created. Only the big/irrelevant
# paths are listed; the handful of small files the Dockerfile needs stay in.
.git
dist
data
vendor
models
docker/.env
**/__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo
.venv
.serena
node_modules
